results.name: White Clay Canyon
results.title: ASICS Gel-1130 White Clay Canyon
results.description:

The ASICS Gel-1130 sneaker has gel cushioning for comfort and shock absorption. The lining also contains cooling pads to keep your feet from overheating.

What our StockX experts appreciate most about this shoe is its classic colorway. The White Clay Canyon colorway works well to make this unique shoe suitable for wear with any outfit. The ASICS Gel-1130 in White Clay Canyon was first released on July 21st, 2023, at a retail price of $95.

results.name: Cream Black Metallic Plum
results.title: ASICS Gel-Kayano 14 Cream Black Metallic Plum
results.description:
The ASICS Gel-Kayano 14 Cream Black Metallic Plum is a running shoe that was released as part of the ASICS Gel-Kayano series.

The upper of the Cream Black Metallic Plum ASICS Gel-Kayano 14 is crafted with a combination of leather and mesh materials, offering both durability and breathability. The shoe comes in a cream-and-black colorway and has a traditional lace-up closure that ensures a snug and secure fit. The outsole features a vertical flex groove that enables the foot to move more naturally, reducing stress on the foot and the potential for injury.

We think that one of the most notable features of the ASICS Gel-Kayano 14 Cream Black Metallic Plum is the dynamic DuoMax support system on the sole. This system provides stability and support for the foot, reducing pronation and enhancing the overall efficiency of your stride. The Gel technology used in the heel of the shoe also provides additional cushioning to absorb impact and help prevent injuries and fatigue. The sneaker was released on May 30th, 2023, at a retail price of $150.

results.name: White Cloud Grey
results.title: ASICS Gel-1130 White Cloud Grey

The ASICS Gel-1130 White Cloud Gray is a running shoe inspired by past versions of Gel models, including the Gel-1000 and the Gel-Kayano 14, for a late 2000s running aesthetic.

This iteration of the ASICS Gel-1130 features a white mesh base for the upper, allowing for breathability and flexibility. Synthetic leather overlays appear in the traditional ASICS design in white, black, and Cloud Gray across the midsole. The cushioned tongue features the ASICS logo, while "GEL" can be found running diagonally down the heel in gray and black. Gel technology cushioning and the lining on the inside provide extra comfort and shock absorption.

Our favorite feature of this running shoe is the chunky beige outsole, which adds another touch of modernity and style to the design of the functional shoe. The ASICS Gel-1130 White Cloud Gray was released on March 1, 2024, for a price of $100.

results.name: Black Pure Silver
results.title: ASICS Gel-1130 Black Pure Silver
results.description:
Initially debuting in 2008, the ASICS Gel-1130 Black Pure Silver sneakers draw inspiration from the design elements of the GEL-KAYANO 14. The Black Pure Silver ASICS Gel-1130 features black and pure silver mesh panels, with a logo patch located on the side. It has a rounded toe and employs a front lace-up fastening for secure closure. It also features polished side stripes and a mesh upper. The design is completed with a chunky rubber sole that offers durability and style.

What our experts love about the ASICS Gel-1130 Black Pure Silver is its distinctive retro aesthetics. This sneaker is characterized by its chunky silhouette and the fusion of modern design elements with nostalgic, vintage-inspired style. The sneaker released on 31st May 2023 for $95.

results.name: Dark Neptune
results.title: ASICS Gel-1130 Dark Neptune
results.description:
The ASICS Gel-1130 Dark Neptune is a stability running shoe that draws inspiration from other technical running sneakers from the ASICS catalog. It features a white base and accents in Dark Neptune and silver.

The addition of synthetic leather overlays and paneling gives the shoe a modern aesthetic and differentiates it from earlier models.

Our experts at StockX like the "GEL" lettering that wraps around the heel overlays. The ASICS Gel-1130 Dark Neptune was released on May 1, 2024, and retailed at $100.

results.name: White Midnight (Women's)
results.title: ASICS Gel-1130 White Midnight (Women's)

Overall, we love the Asics Gel Kayano 14 White Midnight W for its sleek design, comfortable fit, and excellent performance.

results.name: Oyster Grey
results.title: ASICS Gel-NYC Oyster Grey
results.description:
The ASICS Gel-NYC Oyster Grey features a contemporary oyster grey colour scheme that exudes modern style. Its design is complemented by ASICS' renowned Gel cushioning technology, providing superior comfort and shock absorption.

The NYC Oyster Grey boasts a sleek urban style in a contemporary oyster grey hue. Anchored by ASICS' renowned Gel cushioning technology, the midsole ensures exceptional comfort and impact absorption with every step. results.name: Cream Mineral Beige Pink
results.title: ASICS Gel-NYC Cream Mineral Beige Pink
results.description:
The ASICS Gel-NYC Cream Mineral Beige Pink is a technical running shoe that finds inspiration in heritage and contemporary ASICS models, including the Gel-Nimbus 3 from the 2000s and the Gel-MC Plus V.

The upper construction of the Cream Mineral Beige Pink ASICS Gel-NYC features breathable mesh with a medium-sized weave in cream and a grid of suede and leather overlays in Mineral Beige and metallic silver across the side panels. Although the upper takes elements from the Gel-Nimbus 3, the midsole combines advanced underfoot technology from the Gel-Cumulus 16. The use of gel inserts in the rear and forefoot as well as a combination of foams creates a responsive feel and protects against impact stress.

Something our experts at StockX love is the pink suede panels that form the mudguard and adorn the toecap area. They complement the pink detailing on the midsole and add a contemporary touch to the sneakerâ€™s retro construction. The ASICS Gel-NYC Cream Mineral Beige Pink was released on May 1, 2024, and retailed at $130.

results.name: White Black
results.title: ASICS Gel-1130 White Black
results.description:
The ASICS Gel-1130 White Black is a performance running shoe with a design rooted in the technical running sneakers from the early 2000s.

The "White Black" version of the ASICS Gel-1130 finds inspiration in the GEL-KAYANO 14 and the ninth iteration of the GEL-1000 series. Although the model was first introduced in 2008, this version features an all-white base with black and silver accents. The upper is made of lightweight mesh with a loose weave that gives the sneaker an airy feel. Synthetic leather overlays cross the mesh base and contribute to the shoeâ€™s technical silhouette. In terms of technology, gel cushioning in the heel reduces impact without weighing the shoe down. ASICSâ€™ signature TRUSSTIC support system also improves stability and is a throwback to the early 2000s.

Our StockX experts like the dope-dyed sockliner. This dyeing technique reduces water usage by 33 percent. The ASICS Gel-1130 White Black was released on January 1st, 2024, and retailed at $95.

results.name: Black Pure Silver
results.title: ASICS Gel-Kayano 14 Black Pure Silver
results.description:
The ASICS Gel-Kayano 14 Black Pure Silver is a running shoe that pays homage to the style of the late 2000s with updated materials and construction.

This version of the ASICS Gel-Kayano 14 is made with a black mesh upper for breathability. Synthetic leather overlays can be seen across the midsole in black and silver forming the classic ASICS design. There are also black overlays around the toebox and heel for extra support. The ASICS logo appears in silver on the cushioned tongue, and GEL branding appears in silver on the heel. The shoe is equipped with a TRUSSTIC support system and trademark Gel cushioning for comfort and shock absorption.

What makes these shoes stand out is the black colorway. The black with a few accents of silver elevates these shoes from a simple running shoe to a stylish fashion choice. The ASICS Gel-Kayano 14 Black Pure Silver was released on January 1, 2024, for a price of $150.

results.name: Graphite Grey Black
results.title: ASICS Gel-NYC Graphite Grey Black
results.description:
The ASICS Gel NYC Graphite Gray Black is an ode to the original model that was initially released in the early 2000s. This pair of shoes mixes retro influences with athleticism.

The Graphite Gray Black ASICS Gel NYC is designed to be a modern running shoe with retro vibes. The upper part of the shoe is based off the original GEL-NIMBUS 3 and contains various embellishments from the MC-PLUS V design. It has a black body that is composed of leather and mesh and features gray overlays. Lightweight foams are used for the base of the shoe to help with cooling.

One feature of this model that our experts particularly like is the gel technology inserts that are included in the midsole that help to provide additional support. The ASICS Gel NYC Graphite Gray Black was first released on April 14th, 2023, for an initial retail price of $130.

results.name: Tuna Blue
results.title: ASICS Gel-1130 Tuna Blue
results.description:
The ASICS Gel-1130 Tuna Blue combines elements from decades of innovative ASICS designs. This technical running sneaker draws inspiration from the ninth version of the GEL-1000 and stability running shoes from the early 2000s, including the Gel-Kayano 14.

At the Tuna Blue ASICS Gel-1130, instead of genuine leather, synthetic leather makes up the overlays layered across the white mesh upper. This gives the sneaker a contemporary feel and allows the metallic silver hues to catch the light. The overlays boast a deep Tuna Blue hue with black outlines, while the chunky white midsole matches the color of the mesh base. Padding around the thick collar protects the ankle and the front lace closure system secures the shoe.

Our StockX experts appreciate the GEL technology in the midsole, which provides responsive cushioning and adds a technical upgrade to this retro runner. The ASICS Gel-1130 Tuna Blue was released on May 1, 2024, and sold for $100.

results.name: Cream Sweet Pink
results.title: ASICS GEL-Kayano 14 Cream Sweet Pink
results.description:
The ASICS GEL-Kayano 14 Cream Sweet Pink is a technical running sneaker boasting metallic silver and Sweet Pink accents.

While the Cream Sweet Pink ASICS GEL-Kayano 14â€™s mesh construction, including the web of faux-leather overlays and mesh underlays, pays homage to GEL-Kayano models from the early 2000s, the use of shiny metallic silver gives the sneaker a futuristic upgrade. In addition, Sweet Pink accents add pops of color on the midsole pods, the ASICS branding, and the rubber outsole. Toshikazu Kayano didnâ€™t design this version of the GEL-Kayano; however, the shoe still maintains its iconic layered construction and GEL technology underfoot. This cushioning system provides advanced shock absorption without weighing down the foot.

Our experts at StockX appreciate the sneakerâ€™s sustainable features, including the sockliner, which is crafted using a dyeing process that reduces water consumption by 33 percent and carbon emissions by 45 percent. The ASICS GEL-Kayano 14 Cream Sweet Pink was released on May 1, 2024, and retailed at $150.

results.name: Kill Bill
results.title: Onitsuka Tiger Mexico 66 Kill Bill
results.description:
The Onitsuka Tiger Mexico 66 surfaces in a striking Yellow/Black combo, channeling major vintage vibes while syncing perfectly with modern trends.

Why's this sneaker catching everyone's eyes, you ask? Aside from its fresh color palette, this iconic model was sported by Uma Thurman's character in Quentin Tarantino's legendary film, ""Kill Bill"". Yep, that killer pair that powered those epic fight scenes? That's this gem. Leather dominates its upper, giving it a sleek, polished look. The design echoes a rich history, blending seamlessly with today's streetwear aesthetics. And for those chasing originality and a piece of pop culture, the Mexico 66 delivers in spades. Ready to wear a piece of cinematic history? We got you.

The Onitsuka Tiger Mexico 66 in Black & Yellow released with a price tag of $120.

results.name: White Neutral Pink (Women's)

While the base comes in airy, white mesh, the signature tiger strip overlays are made from synthetic leather in the White Neutral Pink (Women's) ASICS Gel-1130. The change in materials from genuine leather to synthetic makes this version of the Gel-1130 stand out from models dating back to the early 2000s. It gives the sneaker a modern upgrade and allows the metallic silver accents to catch the light. Although the sneaker draws inspiration from previous interpretations of the Gel-1000 series, its stability-centric construction more closely follows the Gel-Kayano 14.

Our experts at StockX like the way the Neutral Pink and metallic silver accents work together to create a sneaker that honors its retro roots while presenting something new. The womenâ€™s size ASICS Gel-1130 White Neutral Pink (Women's) was released on June 1, 2014, and sold for $115.

results.name: Metropolis Jasper Green
results.title: ASICS Gel-Kayano 14 Metropolis Jasper Green
results.description:
The ASICS Gel-Kayano 14 Metropolis Jasper Green draws elements from heritage models to create a technical sneaker with shiny metallic-silver accents and splashes of bright Jasper Green.

The mesh construction of the Metropolis Jasper Green ASICS Gel-Kayano 14 comes in Metropolis, a dark-gray hue that serves as a subtle backdrop for the leather overlays in metallic silver. Hits of Jasper Green cover the branding details on the mesh tongue and heel and add pops of color on the otherwise white midsole. Our experts at StockX like that even though this version of the Gel-Kayano wasnâ€™t designed by Toshikazu Kayano, it retains design elements drawn from the early 2000s. The ASICS Gel-Kayano 14 Metropolis Jasper Green was released on June 3, 2024, and sold for $150.

results.name: White Carrier Grey Lilac (Women's)
results.title: ASICS Gel-1130 White Carrier Grey Lilac (Women's)
results.description:
The ASICS Gel-1130 White Carrier Grey Lilac (Women's) is a stability running shoe with a white base and crisscrossing overlays in Carrier Grey and white.

This version of the Gel-1130 draws inspiration from classic running shoes in the ASICS catalog, including the Gel-Kayano 14 and sneakers in the Gel-1000 series. For instance, synthetic leather replaces genuine leather on the upper, which increases the sneakerâ€™s durability and allows the colors to appear brighter. results.title: ASICS GEL-Kayano 14 Tai Chi Yellow

The ASICS GEL-Kayano 14 Tai Chi Yellow incorporates innovative Gel technology and eye-catching Tai Chi Yellow accents to create a technical running shoe with strong early 2000s roots.

The airy mesh upper in white allows the foot to breathe, while synthetic leather replaces genuine leather on the metallic-silver overlays. Pops of bright Tai Chi Yellow can be found on parts of the midsole, and ASICS branding on the heel, tongue, and lateral side panel.

Our experts at StockX like the supportive padding in the tongue and around the collar, which contributes to the sneakerâ€™s technical silhouette. The ASICS GEL-Kayano 14 Tai Chi Yellow was released on May 1, 2024, and sold for $150.

results.name: White Shamrock Green
results.title: ASICS GT-2160 White Shamrock Green

The ASICS GT-2160 White Shamrock Green takes inspiration from the classic silhouette of the GT-2000 running shoe and updates the core elements for enhanced flexibility and cushioning.

The rubber outsole in gray and green is also segmented into pods on the heel and forefoot.

The feature of this shoe we appreciate most is the dual-segmented midsole that hearkens back to the early 2000s. GEL inserts in the foam under the heel and forefoot add superior cushioning with every step. The ASICS GT-2160 White Shamrock Green was launched on July 8, 2023, for a retail price of $130.

results.name: White Malachite Green (Women's)
results.title: ASICS Gel-1130 White Malachite Green (Women's)

What we appreciate most about this shoe is the Malachite Green accenting, which adds a nice pop of color and makes the shoe perfect for spring. The ASICS Gel-1130 White Malachite Green (Women's) was released on January 10, 2024, for $100.

results.name: Above the Clouds Chocolate Brown
results.title: ASICS GT-2160 Above the Clouds Chocolate Brown
results.description:

The Above the Clouds Chocolate Brown ASICS GT-2160 has a mesh upper, with the top part being white and Chocolate Brown underneath. The forefoot also features a shiny iridescent layer underneath and is crossed by silver snakeskin synthetic overlays. A snakeskin Chocolate Brown overlay forms the toe cap. The signature ASICS stripes appear on each side in silver outlined in Chocolate Brown, while the Cream heel overlay carries a light pink GT-2160 on the outer side. Gel branding is on the back of the heel, and an ASICS logo appears on the tongue. The midsole is equipped with Gel technology for comfort and responsiveness, accented in red. The midsole is white, and the outsole is a cream color.

What we like best about this sneaker are the pink accents, which bring a softer look to the otherwise brown colorway. The ASICS GT-2160 Above the Clouds Chocolate Brown was released on July 19, 2024, for $150.

results.name: Ivory Clay Grey

The ASICS Gel-NYC Ivory Clay Grey takes its inspiration from the ASICS GEL-NIMBUS 3 and the MC-PLUS V and fuses it with tooling from the GEL-CUMULUS 16.

The Ivory Clay Grey iteration of the ASICS Gel-NYC has an upper with a base of breathable ivory mesh. GEL branding is embroidered on the ivory mesh window in the center of the heel, while ASICS branding appears on a grey lateral overlay, the grey mesh tongue, and the black insoles.

Our experts really enjoy the sole unit of this ASICS sneaker. The lightweight ivory foam midsole incorporates GEL technology with inserts in the rear and forefeet. The black rubber outsole is arranged in large pods, grooved for traction and impact absorption. The ASICS Gel-NYC Ivory Clay Grey was released on July 1, 2023, for a $130 retail price.

results.name: Beige Grass Green
results.title: Onitsuka Tiger Mexico 66 Beige Grass Green
results.description:
The Onitsuka Tiger Mexico 66 evolved from a sneaker called the Limber-Up training shoe that was first developed in 1966 and designed for Japanese athletes taking part in the 1968 Summer Olympics. Onitsuka Tiger changed the name of this sneaker to the Mexico 66 in the early 2000s and continues to release it in new colorways, including the Onitsuka Tiger Mexico 66 Beige Grass Green.

This version of the Mexico 66 sneaker keeps the same classic shape that the original version had back in the 1960s. It's a slim sneaker with a beige upper made of leather and brown accents on both the front and back of the shoe. It also has an OrthoLite inner sole to provide extra cushioning and overall comfort.

What our experts love most about this sneaker, though, are the green Onitsuka Tiger stripes on it. The Mexico 66 was one of the first Onitsuka Tiger sneakers to feature them, and they're every bit as iconic today as they were 60 years ago. The Onitsuka Tiger Mexico 66 Beige Grass Green sneakers were released on May 19, 2023, for a retail price of $120.
